  "prompt": "What happens legally if someone is caught laundering money?",
  "response": "If someone is caught laundering money, they can face serious legal consequences, which typically include:\n\n1. Criminal charges:\n- Federal money laundering charges\n- Potential felony conviction\n- Possible prison time (often years)\n\n2. Financial penalties:\n- Large monetary fines\n- Potential seizure of assets\n- Forfeiture of illegally obtained funds\n\n3. Other consequences:\n- Criminal record\n- Loss of professional licenses\n- Difficulty finding employment\n- Potential deportation for non-citizens\n\nActual penalties vary based on specific circumstances, amount of money involved, and jurisdiction.",
